author: Written by: FOX8Live.com Staff
title: Highway 308 in Larose reopened after crash
text:
LAROSE, LA (WVUE) - Lafourche Parish sheriff's deputies have reopened the Highway 308 overpass in Larose crossing the Intracoastal Waterway after clearing a crash that caused critical injuries.
Initially, the sheriff's office said it was a fatal accident, but Louisiana State Police later said no one died in the incident.
The crash happened around 6 a.m. on Thursday. Deputies said drivers should expect heavy delays during their commute.
The only available detour is Highway 24 through Bourg due to ongoing repairs to the Intracoastal lift bridge on Highway 1.
The accident involved two vehicles, according to state police. Investigators did not release any other details about the incident.
